"The Last First: Winter K2" (Amir Bar-Lev, US, UK) [Documentary Premieres]
 — The race to grab the last great prize in mountaineering, K2 in winter, left five dead. It exposed deep fault lines in alpinism today: pressures from commercialization, toxic effects of social media, and long-brewing tensions between those who’ve been marginalized and those who’ve always basked in the sport’s glory. World Premiere. Documentary.

Owen Gleiberman         https://variety.com/2026/film/reviews/the-last-first-winter-k2-review-sundance-1236637413/

